election_record.label: New York 1806 State Senate, Western District

overview.note: Freegift Annin is an amalgamation of two candidates.

sub_unit.name: Angelica
sub_unit.note: Allegany county was formed from Genesee county in 1806, and Angelica was the only town in the new county. Most sources list returns from Allegany with those from Genesee in 1806.

sub_unit.name: Cayuga
sub_unit.note: John Grover, Jr. received 1 vote as John Grover.
John MacWhorter received 3 votes as J. MacWhorter.
Joseph Annin received 4 votes as J. Annin.
Evans Wharry received 3 votes as E. Wherry.
Freegift Patchin received 3 votes as F. Patchin and 2 votes as Freeman Patchin.

sub_unit.note: Salmon Buell received 8 votes as Solomon Buell.
Nathan Smith received 2 votes as Nathaniel Smith.
Jacob Gebhard received 1 vote as Joseph Gephard.
John MacWhorter received 1 vote as Joseph MacWhorter.
Evans Wharry received 1 vote as Evans Wharter.

sub_unit.name: Onondaga
sub_unit.note: Salmon Buell received 7 votes as Solomon Buell and 2 votes as Samuel Buell.
Nathan Smith received 2 votes as Nathaniel Smith.
Jacob Gebhard received 2 votes as John Gebhard.
John MacWhorter received 3 votes as James MacWhorter.
Joseph Annin received 1 vote as Josept Annin and 2 votes as Annin.
Freegift Patchin received 1 vote as Freelove Patchin.
Thaddeus M. Wood received 1 vote as T.M. Wood.

The official canvass of votes lists 516 votes for Nathan Smith, 717 votes for John MacWhorter, 417 votes for Joseph Annin, 444 votes for Evans Wharry, and 411 votes for Freegift Patchin in Onondaga county.
